data.text: @USFBulls2 @TallyBull No, you re definitely not alone. A friend of mine had very similar to what you experienced. Keith and I were more tired the first night but nothing other than that. You're through the worst if it, hopefully!
@NancyCarrow @TallyBull Thank you :). Yeah, I didn’t expect it to be like that. Talking to friends/Kelsey across the board experienced similar symptoms, so at least I know I’m not alone.
@DuOughton Man, I got more than I bargained for last night. Wow
@USFBulls2 @TallyBull Wow,, that stinks. I'm glad you're feeling better now. It's wierd how people have differing effects from the same vaccine. Hope you continue to feel better.
@NancyCarrow @TallyBull Lots of water and Tylenol saved me haha

@NancyCarrow @TallyBull Last night was really rough. Towards the end of the game my whole body started feeling really achy. Woke up around 3 am with the worst hot/cold flashes I’ve ever had. Fever dreams. 6 layers of blankets and still shivering. Finally got some relief around 6-7 am. I feel ok now

@TallyBull Yeah, my fiancé got hers back in Jan. She was out of commission for 2-3 days. Granted, her immune system gets worked with any sickness. I usually recover quicker than her. I’m hoping with a good nights rest and that I can sleep in tomorrow, I’ll be okay when I wake up.
@NancyCarrow @TallyBull Thank you. Me too. I’m trying to finish the Rays game but I’m dosing off. Loaded up with water and Tylenol, it’s helping for sure.
@TallyBull @USFBulls2 Drink lots of water and tylenol every 3-4 hrs. Hoping you feel better in the morning.
@USFBulls2 FWIW I did too but was 100% two days after, good luck with it
